#X text 40 20 osc-receive.pd --- OSC input for the Shrine sound engine.;
#X text 40 40 Real contract (edge-node firmware + osc-sim/generator.py):;
#X text 40 58 /shrine/node/{0..3} -> 5 floats: self_stdev(=cap presence) carrier_mag(dropped) gsr_mag0 gsr_mag1 gsr_mag2.;
#X text 40 76 node id 0-indexed -> pad cap-(N+1). The 3 gsr slots map to global pairs via;
#X text 40 94 NODE_GSR_MAPPING = node0:[0 1 2] node1:[3 4 0] node2:[5 1 3] node3:[2 4 5] (see leds/sensor_state.py).;
#X text 40 112 Emits buses cap-1..4 and gsr-mag-0..5 in 0-1. Normalization lives in normcap/normgsr.;
#X text 470 365 node id arrives as a symbol from oscparse -- convert via makefilename + select then prepend as a float and route.;
